# Example local layout file.
#
# This is the layout `d restore` applies (also known as `display-restore.sh`).
# Goal: physical display is main at native resolution. If your remote layout
# uses a BetterDisplay virtual display, you can have it removed here too.
#
# Optional directive this layout supports (lines starting with `#`):
#
#   # betterdisplay-discard: <args>
#       After applying the displayplacer command, run `betterdisplaycli
#       discard <args>` (looped until nothing is left to discard, to clean
#       up any accumulated duplicates). Used to fully remove the virtual
#       display created by `d remote`.
#
# Replace this by running:
#   ../scripts/capture-layout.sh local
#
# A working local example for Studio Display + ScreensRemote:
#   # betterdisplay-discard: --type=VirtualScreen --name=ScreensRemote
#   displayplacer "id:s1879776955 res:3200x1800 hz:60 color_depth:8 enabled:true scaling:on origin:(0,0) degree:0"
displayplacer "id:your-display-id res:your-mode scaling:on origin:(0,0) degree:0" # PLACEHOLDER
